The paper discusses the development of a neuromorphic oculomotor controller for a biomimetic robotic head, which involves real-time processing of noisy information in a changing environment. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.NE (neural and evolutionary computing), cs.RO (robotics), cs.CV (computer vision), cs.AI (artificial intelligence), and cs.SY (systems and control). However, given the focus on spiking neural networks and their use in controlling the robotic head, cs.NE is the most likely sub-category. The other sub-categories are also relevant due to the use of computer vision and artificial intelligence techniques in the development of the controller, as well as the focus on control systems and robotics.
